Project 1: Boston & Seattle Airbnb Data Analysis¶

Yu Tao 2021/03/22

1. Business Understanding¶

In this notebook, I will look at the Boston and Seattle Airbnb data, and try to answer several business questions:

  • (1) How does the price of an Airbnb home vary by time?
  • (2) What is the monthly occupancy of a common Airbnb home?
  • (3) How much does an Airbnb home cost, given its property and room type?
  • (4) How does the neighborhood affect the price of the Airbnb home?
  • (5) How to predict the price of an Airbnb home give some of its properties?
  • (6) How are super hosts and regular hosts reviewed by their customers?

The answers to these business questions can be helpful for the Airbnb hosts to better understand the values of their properties, and are also important for the customers to get a satisfactory Airbnb service that meets their own requirements. I will handle these problems using descriptive statistics and a linear regression model.

2. Data Understanding¶

The Boston and Seattle Airbnb data are obtained from Kaggle. The following Airbnb activity is included in both datasets:

  • Listings, including full descriptions and average review score
  • Reviews, including unique id for each reviewer and detailed comments
  • Calendar, including listing id and the price and availability for that day

I will begin by importing the necessary libraries and loading the datasets.

3. Prepare Data¶

Depending on the business questions, we need to prepare the data in different ways, to reiterate, here are the questions we posted before, we will handle them one at a time.

  • (1) How does the price of an Airbnb home vary by time?
  • (2) What is the monthly occupancy of a common Airbnb home?
  • (3) How much does an Airbnb home cost, given its property and room type?
  • (4) How does the neighborhood affect the price of the Airbnb home?
  • (5) How to predict the price of an Airbnb home give some of its properties?
  • (6) How are super hosts and regular hosts reviewed by their customers?

3.1 Distribiton of Airbnb price¶

To answer this question, we'll need to focus on the price, monthly price and weekly price columns in the listings dataframes. We need to convert the values in these columns to float type and remove the dollar symbol, let's do it now.

In [19]:
# convert some price values to float type
df_sea_listings["price"]=df_sea_listings.price.str.replace('$','').str.replace(',','').astype(float)
df_sea_listings["weekly_price"]=df_sea_listings.weekly_price.str.replace('$','').str.replace(',','').astype(float)
df_sea_listings["monthly_price"]=df_sea_listings.monthly_price.str.replace('$','').str.replace(',','').astype(float)
df_sea_listings["extra_people"]=df_sea_listings.extra_people.str.replace('$','').str.replace(',','').astype(float)

df_bos_listings["price"]=df_bos_listings.price.str.replace('$','').str.replace(',','').astype(float)
df_bos_listings["weekly_price"]=df_bos_listings.weekly_price.str.replace('$','').str.replace(',','').astype(float)
df_bos_listings["monthly_price"]=df_bos_listings.monthly_price.str.replace('$','').str.replace(',','').astype(float)
df_bos_listings["extra_people"]=df_bos_listings.extra_people.str.replace('$','').str.replace(',','').astype(float)

I will plot the price distribution of all Airbnb homes in Boston and Seattle, also I set the limit at $500/night.

For monthly price and weekly price, we'll need to first merge the listings and calendar dataframes, then groupby either month or week and find the average price of Airbnb.

In [21]:
# merge listings and calendar dataframe
df_sea_listings=df_sea_listings.rename(columns={'id':'listing_id'})
df_bos_listings=df_bos_listings.rename(columns={'id':'listing_id'})
df_sea_ls_cal=pd.merge(df_sea_listings, df_sea_calendar, on='listing_id', how='inner')
df_bos_ls_cal=pd.merge(df_bos_listings, df_bos_calendar, on='listing_id', how='inner')
In [22]:

5. Evaluate the Results¶

From the price distribution of AirBnb homes in Boston and Seattle, Generally, an AirBnb home in Boston costs 60 dollars more than one Seattle. The most common price of an AirBnb home in Boston ranges from 50 dollars to 200 dollars, whereas in Seattle, you can typically find a good place to stay with no more than 150 dollars.

From the monthly and weekly price distributions of an AirBnb home in Boston and Seattle. Boston sees its peak monthly price in September and October, when the average price of an AirBnb home can reach to around 230 dollars. My assumption is that this price increase results from the high demand from the students. As we know, Boston has many famous colleges and universities, many new students coming in the fall semester (usually in September) might choose to temporarily live in an AirBnb home when they first settle in Boston. Compared with the Bostons monthly price, we see the Seattles monthly price peaks in the summer, with an average cost of around 150 dollars, this increase might be related to the tourists visiting.

In terms of weekly price, these two cities share a similar trait, which is that there is a slight increase in the price during the weekend. For a customer visiting Boston/Seattle, it is likely that you will pay 12 dollars more per day compared with weekdays price.

From the price history of AirBnb homes in Boston and Seattle, the Seattle data was collected in the 2016 calendar year, whereas the Boston data was collected from 201609 to 201709, in both curves we can see the price oscillation based on week. While the AirBnb price in Seattle looks more stable, there are some interesting changes in the Bostons AirBnb average price. First, there is a dramatic decrease in price from 201609 to 201701, with the average price dropping from around 260 dollars to around 180 dollars. Second, there is a peak price seen on April 17th, 2017, on this day (also days before and after it) we observe a 50 dollars increase in the cost. I checked what happened in Boston on that day out of curiosity, and I suspect its related to the Boston Marathon, when many participants flew into the city.

From the monthly occupancy of AirBnb homes in Boston and Seattle, we can see that except in September and October in Boston, you can easily book an AirBnb home because the occupancy in both cities are below 50%. Boston has an occupancy of around 50%, and Seattle has an occupancy of around 35%. However, in September and October in Boston, the occupancy can sometimes reach to up to 70%, and also the prices at this time period are higher as we see in the previous section.

From the counts of different room types and property types that were included in our AirBnb data, I calculated the average price for these different options. In Boston, if your choice is an entire apartment or house, that usually means an average cost of 250 dollars to 350 dollars. If this exceeds your limit, there are also options for a private apartment/house room, which is worth around 90 dollars per night. In Seattle, a private apartment/house room has a similar price of around 80 dollars. For an entire place in Seattle, it is often cheaper than Boston and usually costs no more than 200 dollars.

From the neighborhood price plot, we see that in Boston, places in Leather District and The Westin Boston Waterfront are higher in price, whereas in Seattle, places in Southeast Magnolia and Portage Bay are much expensive.

From the ratings on super hosts vs. regular hosts, on a scale of 010, we can see that, on average, super hosts are better rated in terms of information accuracy, home cleanliness, check-in procedure, guest communication, home location and experience value. Super hosts got ratings between 9.6 to 10, whereas regular hosts got ratings between 9.1 to 9.7.

From the correlation figure, we can see that the price is more correlated with some variables like bathrooms, bedrooms, beds, guests allowed, and also the room type. I used a linear regression model on the Seattle AirBnb data and derived an equation: price = estimate * variables where you can calculate an expected AirBnb price given the variables, this models accuracy is around 52 percent. It is noted that this model is not 100 percent accurate, there are many extra factors that can affect the price of the AirBnb home.
